(1. PURPOSE) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The application provides a multi-user, multi-tenant web system for tracking ammunition) Tj T*
(reloading components, inventory lots, user-defined cartridge recipes, production batches,) Tj T*
(storage containers, QR labels, performance/quality results, backups, exports, and audit) Tj T*
(history.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The primary goal remains traceability. The application shall allow a user to determine:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  - What component items were defined.) Tj T*
(  - What inventory lots were acquired.) Tj T*
(  - Which inventory lots were active, reserved, consumed, adjusted, depleted, returned, or) Tj T*
(    lost.) Tj T*
(  - Which recipe a batch was produced from.) Tj T*
(  - Which exact lots were reserved and consumed by a batch.) Tj T*
(  - Which containers currently hold completed cartridges from a batch.) Tj T*
(  - Which quantities have been cleared from emptied containers.) Tj T*
(  - What performance and quality information was recorded for each batch.) Tj T*
(  - How batch performance contributes to recipe-level evaluation.) Tj T*
(  - Which safety or traceability warnings were acknowledged.) Tj T*
(  - Which important operations occurred in audit history.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The application stores user-entered load data. It does not recommend powder charges, infer) Tj T*
(safe loads, certify that a recipe is safe, or replace published manuals or manufacturer) Tj T*
(data.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The architecture and data model shall remain open to future analytics, source comparison,) Tj T*
(and import workflows, but recommendation-like behavior shall not be part of the current) Tj T*
(implementation.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
