(7.3 Active Lot Rule) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(For a given user and item, only one non-depleted lot may be active at a time.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The user can create additional inactive lots. A new active lot can explicitly replace the) Tj T*
(currently active lot when `replace_active` is requested. The replaced lot is deactivated) Tj T*
(and audited.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(An active depleted lot is automatically deactivated.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(7.4 Opened Date) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(`opened_on` is system-managed.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The lot is marked opened when it is active and first has inventory drawdown through) Tj T*
(reservation or consumption. A creation payload cannot set `opened_on`.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(If a lot had prior drawdown while inactive and the user later activates it, the system sets) Tj T*
(`opened_on` at activation.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
