(2. Transitioning the batch to `PRODUCED` commits all reserved inventory as consumed.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Reservation effects:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  - Increase lot `reserved_quantity`.) Tj T*
(  - Reduce derived available quantity.) Tj T*
(  - Create `BatchInventoryReservation` rows with status `RESERVED`.) Tj T*
(  - Audit inventory reservation.) Tj T*
(  - Mark an active lot opened if this is its first drawdown.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Production completion effects:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  - Decrease lot `reserved_quantity`.) Tj T*
(  - Increase lot `consumed_quantity`.) Tj T*
(  - Create `BatchInventoryConsumption` rows.) Tj T*
(  - Mark reservations `CONSUMED`.) Tj T*
(  - Mark depleted lots depleted and inactive.) Tj T*
(  - Audit inventory consumption.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Performance/quality data cannot be recorded while the batch remains `UNDER PRODUCTION`.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
