(22. ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA SUMMARY) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The application is currently aligned with these acceptance criteria:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  - A user can register, log in, log out, and access only their own data.) Tj T*
(  - A user can reset a password through an operator-triggered local reset workflow.) Tj T*
(  - A user can create, edit, list, search, filter, and archive Items.) Tj T*
(  - A user can add lot-based Inventory.) Tj T*
(  - Powder inventory can be entered in common mass units and consumed in grains.) Tj T*
(  - Count inventory requires whole-number count quantities.) Tj T*
(  - Depleted lots remain historically visible.) Tj T*
(  - Inventory can be adjusted through audited correction records.) Tj T*
(  - A user can create a Recipe for one completed cartridge.) Tj T*
(  - A Recipe can reference exact component Items.) Tj T*
(  - A Recipe can include source metadata and safety acknowledgements.) Tj T*
(  - A Recipe can be private or public by public link.) Tj T*
(  - Public recipe access does not expose private tenant data.) Tj T*
(  - A user can create a Batch from a Recipe.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch reserves inventory under production.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch consumes inventory when moved to `PRODUCED`.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch cannot override insufficient inventory.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch can be cancelled only with explicit return/loss accounting.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch can be assigned across one or more containers.) Tj T*
(  - A Container can hold one or more batches with acknowledgement.) Tj T*
(  - Container capacity limits are enforced.) Tj T*
(  - Batch storage and depletion states update from container assignments and container) Tj T*
(    state.) Tj T*
(  - QR codes can be generated for batch and recipe identification.) Tj T*
(  - A Batch can have one consolidated performance/quality record after production.) Tj T*
(  - Recipe pages can aggregate batch performance data.) Tj T*
(  - Important changes are audited.) Tj T*
(  - The system can be migrated through Alembic.) Tj T*
(  - The system can be backed up.) Tj T*
(  - Tenant data can be exported as JSON or CSV.) Tj T*
(  - API and Selenium tests cover major workflows.) Tj T*
